inn1.comm: good length outside off, shaping away from the right hander, left alone
short of a length outside off, guided to third man
on middle and off, defended on the off side
short of a good length on middle, gets on the back foot and defends
full on middle and leg, makes room but the bowler chases him, dropped on the off side for a quick single
full outside off, driven firmly, but straight to cover
short on middle, chopped straight to point
chases him outside leg again, pushed wide of mid-on for a single
down the leg side, tries to flick it away fine, misses, given a wide
beaten! Good length on the off stump, hit the pitch hard and swung away just as the batsmen tried to defend that off the back foot
short of a length on the off, struck firmly to short cover off the back foot
short on middle and  dealt with appropriately, gets on the back foot and pulls it away over midwicket for a boundary
fuller on the off stump, defended into the off side
just a fraction full on middle and leg, makes room and tries to loft it over the bowlers head, misses and the ball goes just over the stumps to the keeper
full on the pads, pushed uppishly towards deep midwicket for a single
good length on the off stump, opens the face to play it to point

gone! Goes for a wild swing over long-on, fraction full on the off stump, is not to the pitch, the ball sails high and Vettori at mid-off takes a well judged catch after waiting for ages for it to get to him
full on the pads and cashes in, stays his ground and drives it beautifully between mid-on and midwicket for a boundary
short of a length outside off, cut away to third man for a single
pushed away off the back foot wide of square leg for a well-run two
short of a length on middle, mistimes a pull wide of midwicket
on a good length on middle, driven wide of mid-on for a single
short of a length on middle, makes room and chops it down straight to cover
full on middle and leg, makes room and drives it straight to mid-off for a single
short on the off stump, tries to run it down to third man, gets an inside edge onto his thighs and they take a quick single
Gone!! Full outside off and moves away, Ponting's fishing for it off the front foot, gets a thin edge straight to the keeper. New Zealand have struck early here
full on the off stump, pushed straight to cover
on middle and off, pushed off the front foot to cover again
shot! Good length on the off stump, makes room, comes down the track and lofts it cleanly over mid-off for a one bounce four
full outside leg stump, tries to glance it down fine, misses, given a wide
short on middle, dropped off the back foot short of midwicket for a quick single
short of a length outside off, gets a thick inside edge wide of mid-on for a single as he tries to cart that over extra cover
short on middle and off, pushed short of mid-off for a single
good length outside off, opens the face to guide it to point
driven off the front foot wide of mid-on for a single
yorker length on middle, dug out wide of mid-on for single

gone, wild swing and pays the price! Full on middle and leg, Hussey makes room to smash it over mid-on, it came back in a a touch and crashed into leg stump. Australia in a spot of bother now at 30 for 3
good length outside off, good testing line, left alone
good length on middle and leg, driven to deep midwicket for a couple
flicked away to fine leg for a single
short of a good length on middle, swinging away, gets a leading edge wide of point as he tries to work that away towards midwicket
mistimes a pull wide of midwicket for a single
dropped, short of a length outside off, cut away powerfully wide of Guptill at point who dives full length to his right and fails to hold on to a tough one-handed chance
whipped off the back foot wide of square leg, short on middle and leg
driven through midwicket for a couple
short on middle and leg, tries to pull it away powerfully over midwicket, mistimes it again to only get a single
short of a length outside off, tries ti cut but gets an under-edge on the bounce to the keeper
good length outside off, eased off the front foot to deep cover
good length on middle and leg, jagged back in sharply, tries to flick it away on the leg side, is rapped on the pads but the ball seemed to be sliding down leg
full on leg stump, pushed wide of mid-on for a single
almost had a wicket off his first ball, bowled on a good length outside off, tried to slap it back past the bowler, got the outside edge that just evaded point
manages to connect well this time, full on middle and leg, coming in, slogged away well wide of midwicket for a boundary
short of a good length on the middle stump, pushed off the back foot to long-on
shot! Marginally short outside off, cut away wide of third man where Mills dives well to keep the batsmen to a couple
slower ball bowled on a good length outside off from round the wicket, run down to third man for a single
short outside off, opens the face to keep the third-man fielder busy again
yorker on the off stump, dug out to mid-on
and again, similar length but played wide of the bowler to long-on
beaten! Good length on the off stump and zipped away off the pitch just as Hussey came forward to defend
fuller outside off, driven on the up straight to short cover
short outside off, dabbed down to third man for a single
full on the off stump, driven down the ground to long-on for a single
big one! Full on middle, length ball and Haddin cashes in, gets under it and dismisses it over the deep midwicket boundary for a massive six
full outside off, driven firmly to long-off
round the wicket to the left-hander, on middle, turned away to fine leg for a single
too full there and gets the treatment once again, on the off stump and its driven back powerfully to bisect the gap between long-on and long-off for a boundary
tries to slog it away towards deep midwicket this time, gets a thick inside edge
slower ball bowled on a good length outside off, run down to third man
gone! What an inspired bowling change!! Short on middle and off, there to hit, he pulls it away straight to Diamanti stationed perfectly at deep midwicket. Big wicket for New Zealand
tossed up on middle and leg, flicked away behind square for a single
quicker on middle and off, driven straight to short cover
tossed up on middle and leg, comes down the track and drives it straight to midwicket
bowled flat and quick on middle, defended back to the bowler
on middle and off, comes down the track and pushes it to midwicket. Excellent over
beaten! That held its line but Ferguson played inside the line there, didn't miss the outside edge by much
bouncer banged in on middle, Ferguson ducks under it
good length on middle and off, tries to drive it off the back foot wide of mid-on, gets struck on the pads in line, but was probably a touch high
slower ball on middle and off, pushed wide of midwicket for a single
full outside off, steered to deep cover

missed runout, tries to work it away on the leg side, rushes down the pitch after being struck on the pads, Elliot gathers the ball cleanly but fails to thrown down the stumps with an under-arm flick. Ferguson was miles short
driven to deep cover for a single
quicker ball outside off, drives it wide of short cover for a single
short on the off stump, pushed off the back foot to long-off
paddled uppishly towards fine leg where a fumble allows them to come back for the third. O'Brien the culprit there
50 for Haddin, short and wide, cut away wide of deep cover for a couple. He's had a good series with the bat
fired in quick on middle and off, struck to deep cover again. He's scored a fifty while no one lese has yet gotten into double figures
down the leg side for a wide this time, false start to a new over
better, yorker length on middle, dragged down to long-on
full outside off, sliced away uppishly just short of deep point
slower ball on the off stump, swatted down the ground to long-on
short of a good length outside off, punched down to deep cover
full outside off, guided to point from the crease
yorker length on middle again, just about manages to dig it out, doesn't miss the stumps by much
swings and doesn't miss the off stump by too far, short of a length outside off and he tries to slog it away over midwicket, misses
short of a length outside off, driven through the off side to deep cover
short of a length on middle and off, chipped off the back foot towards long-on
full and quick on the off stump, driven to extra cover who's right on the circle
flighted on middle and leg, chipped uppishly towards deep midwicket
just wide of the midwicket fielder who flings himself to his right but fails to reach an uppish drive off the front foot
overpitched ball outside off, Haddin waits for it and smashes it back over the bowlers head for a powerful boundary
full again and struck firmly down the ground to long-off
full on middle and leg, yorker length, tries to flick it away fine, manages to dig it out on the leg side
short of a length outside off, cut away towards deep point off the backfoot for a couple
good ball, banged in short on middle and leg, tries to pull it away over midwicket, misses
low full toss on the off stump, driven straight to mid-on for a single
good length outside off, driven firmly to long-off
bowled flat outside off, walks across to paddle it fine, gets a top-edge that just falls short of short third man

struck firmly to cover where Ros Taylor pulls off a good diving save, but still cannot prevent Haddin to make it for a single at the strikers end. He returns a good throw to the keeper but Haddin's well in
tossed up on middle, comes down the track and drives it straight to long-on
flighted on middle and leg, down the track and lofts it cleanly over the bowlers head for a boundary between long-on and long-off
makes room and chops it towards deep cover
inside edge and four, full outside off and he tries to swing that away on the leg side, evades the short-fine fielder to the boundary
highly effective, in the slot again, on the off stump, dragged well wide of mid-on for a boundary
his most convincing shot so far, full on middle, makes room and drives it cleanly down the ground to beat mid-on to the boundary
driven to deep cover for a single
excellent yorker on middle, tries to dig it out into the leg side, gets an inside edge and they scramble a single
full outside off, makes room and steers it to deep cover
full toss outside off, driven wide of long-off for a couple
good length outside off, driven firmly wide of deep cover for two more
third man is up and he takes full toll, full outside off stump, he makes room to place it beautifully between short third and point for a boundary
dropped, Vettori puts it down at midwicket as Ferguson tries to heave that over him, timed his jump well but failed to hold on, tough chance
this powerplay has cost New Zealand, low full toss on leg stump, makes room and lofts it over mid-on for a one bounce four
yorker on middle and leg, drilled to mid-on for a single
low full toss outside off, driven to deep cover for a single to get to his maiden ODI fifty, good innings
where was Haddin? Full on middle, in the slot, a meaty half-volley, Haddin stays his ground, gets under it, and deposits it into the stands over long-on
driven down the ground to long-off
poor fielding by Jeetan Patel, low full toss on middle, driven wide of midwicket and Patel in the deep slides but ends up deflecting the ball to the boundary
full on middle, flicked away to deep square leg
yorker on the off stump, dug out into the leg side for a single
shot! Full on the pads, Haddin walks across and paddles it over short fine for a boundary
tries to do something similar there but the ball simply isn't there to hit, banged in short on purpose outside off to take Haddin by surprise
you can't feed the batsman with length balls at this stage, full on the off stump and Haddin dismisses that over long-on, easily done, all power in the shot
full outside off, sliced away behind point for a couple
tries to heave it over midwicket this time, misses, stifled appeal by McCullum but the umpire shakes his head
good length outside off, tries to smash it back over the bowlers head, gets a thick outside edge towards third man where Jeetan Patel keeps them down to two

inn2.comm: runs straightaway, short and wide, cut over point for a couple
bowled 'im!! Massive blow! Full on middle and leg and swung away, McCullum played down the wrong line there, tried to swing it away over midwicket, missed and the stumps took a beating!
short of a good length outside off, guided to point off the back foot
on middle and off, swinging away, defended on the front foot to cover
bouncer banged in on middle, Fulton ducks with some difficulty
short of a good length outside off, mistimes a back-foot drive back to the bowler
swung in sharply from Bracken, landed on a good length on the off, hit on the arm as he tries to fend that away
big one, short on middle, Guptill rocks back and pulls it away well over deep square leg for a massive six
good length on middle and off, defended watchfully on the front foot
full on the pads, flicked away to fine leg for a single
shot! Fraction full outside off, Fulton hits through the line to drive that uppishly between cover and point for a boundary
excellent batting, in the slot, full on the off stump, driven powerfully down the ground to the boundary, mid-off had no chance there
beautifully played, Hilfenhaus strays on the pads, Guptill gets on the back foot and flicks it away wide of fine leg for a boundary
in front of square this time, too straight by Hilfenhaus, driven through midwicket for three runs
well bowled, good length on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
that's disappeared, just marginally short on the off stump, Fulton pikced the length really early to pull it away into the stands over deep midwicket
full toss down the leg side, Fulton misses an opportunity there, given a wide
another one into the stands, Fulton is dealing in sixes here, full on middle and leg, he stays his ground and lofts that cleanly over long-on for another big one
full on middle and leg, flicked away to deep square leg
full on the pads, chipped uppishly towards deep square leg
good length on middle and off, dropped on the off side for a quick single

gone! Fulton's thrown away his wicket! Short of a length on the off stump, he makes room to cut that over point, gets the top-edge and Ferguson runs a few steps back to pouch an good catch. Now that changes things
short on middle and leg, defended on the leg side
chipped uppishly towards midwicket for a couple
short of a length outside off, punched firmly off the back foot wide of point for three runs
short on middle and leg and Guptill cashes in, hooks it over fine leg for a massive six
short of a length on the off stump, pushed off the back foot towards cover
taken by surprise there, brilliantly bowled bouncer, rapped Taylor on the arms on its way towards first slip
shot! Short and wide, cut away fiercely through point for a boundary, that reached the ropes in the blink of an eye

he's gifted his wicket here after a superb shot the previous ball! Good length outside off, tries to swat it over the bowler's head, gets the top-edge and Hussey at cover takes a well-judged catch as it takes forever to come down
short on middle and leg, pulled away towards deep square leg
well bowled, good length on middle and leg, tries to push it back to the bowler, gets a thick outside edge to point
straying on the pads, flicked away really fine to the boundary, a pressure-relieving shot that
good length outside off and Guptill smashes that over extra cover for a flat six, that landed straight on the ropes
short on middle and leg, pulled away towards deep square leg for a single
edged and gone! Elliot is gone first ball! Fishing for it outside off, short and wide, tried to run it down to third man, got a thin edge straight to Haddin
full on the off stump, defended on the front foot to the bowler, watchfully played

run out, Guptill's running out of partners here, full on the off stump, defended towards point and they attempt a quick single, Ponting runs in, picks the ball cleanly and throws down the stumps at the striker's end in one motion to find Broom well short of his ground. Could that be the decisive blow?
beaten straightaway, bowled at 148.2 kmph, full outside off, he drives through the line but fails to make contact
full outside off, sliced away to third man
short of a length on middle, tries to pull it behind square, gets the top edge over the keeper, Hilfenhaus dives superbly to his left to prevent a boundary
short of a good length on the off stump, defended on the back foot
good length on the off stump, driven back to the bowler
short of a length on middle, pulled towards deep square leg for a single
beaten! Some inward movement here for Siddle, good length outside off and came in just a touch, Mills played inside the line to that one, and predictably missed
going away this time, short of a good length outside off, played away from his body there, and failed to make contact
banged in short on middle, tries to run it down to third man, is hit on the elbow
short outside off, makes room to cut, gets an under-edge just wide of the stumps
what a catch!! Good length on the off stump, makes room and chips it lethargically over mid-off, Michael Hussey runs back to his right, leaps and plucks it with one hand to complete a neat catch!
Guptill continues his merry way, low full toss on leg stump, driven uppishly wide of mid-on for a boundary
good length on middle and off, defended on the off side and they set off for a quick run
short and a touch too wide, given, bowled at 147 kmph
beaten this time, good bounce for the bowler, spat off the pitch after landing on a good length outside off, tried to cut, missed
edged and four, short and wide, upper-cut over second slip, slashed really hard there and got the result
full on the off stump, drilled down the ground to mid-off, decide against the single
short on middle and leg, tucked away behind square and they get a well-run two
short of a length outside off, cut away to deep cover
too wide and gets the treatment, cut away fiercely, well wide of third man for a boundary
full outside off stump, tries to push off the front foot, the ball just about beats the outside edge
and again, tries to open the face to run it down to third man, misses
on middle and leg, driven straight to midwicket
nipped back in, pitched full on middle and leg and was sliding down as it struck him on the pads as he was attempting a drive through midwicket
struck away uppishly towards deep square leg, excellent fifty for Guptill but he's ran out of partners.

short of a good length outside off, prodded at it off the back foot, went through to the keeper and the Australians went up immediately, there was certainly a noise but the umpire wasn't convince. We'll need a replay to confirm that. There was no deviation, nor was there a nick
dropped on the off side for a quick single
just a fraction short and gets punished, on the off stump and Guptill drags it well wide of midwicket for a boundary
slower ball bowled full on middle, driven off the front foot between deep midwicket and deep square leg for a couple
bowled full on the leg stump from wide of the crease, tried to glace it fine, hit on the pads and they get a leg bye
short of a good length on middle and leg, tries to whip it away off his hips, gets an inside edge onto his pads
full outside off, driven firmly on the bounce wide of the bowler for a single
shot! Full outside off, driven uppishly towards deep extra cover for a couple
short on middle and leg, pulled away powerfully wide of midwicket for a boundary, good confident short from Diamanti
he's looking good here, short of a good length outside off, chopped down over point for three runs, Siddle dives at deep point to drag the ball just back in
full and a touch too wide, the batsman reaches for it, misses
superb shot! Good length on middle and leg, too straight, he turns it away behind square, well wide of short fine leg for a boundary. The visitors are fighting back well here
good length outside off, slashes hard at it, misses
played and missed, short of a good length outside off, prodded at it, failed to connect
short of a good length outside off, opens the face to play it wide of point for a single
full on middle and off, tries to drive it down the ground to long-on, gets a thick outside edge towards third man
short on the off stump and swung away, tried to defend off the back foot, beat the outside edge
lands on a good length on the off stump, plays across the line, gets a thick edge over point for a couple towards third man
firmly struck, full outside off, drilled down the ground for a single
short of a length outside off, tries to cut that over point, is into the shot too early, misses
full on the pads, flicked away through square leg, fine leg takes some time to reach the ball and the batsmen are back for the second
pushed to David Hussey at cover and they take a quick single, a direct hit would have been close
short of a length outside off, plays and misses
slapped in front of square, towards deep cover
